                            <comment id="13046906" author="davelatham" created="Thu, 9 Jun 2011 23:01:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve seen the same thing happen with auto flush off, when calling flushCommits.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13047754" author="nspiegelberg" created="Fri, 10 Jun 2011 23:14:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch should apply cleanly to 0.89, 0.90, &amp;amp; 0.92.  I strongly recommend anyone who needs reliable Puts apply this patch to their build.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13047773" author="davelatham" created="Fri, 10 Jun 2011 23:43:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for taking on this issue, Nicolas.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think it&apos;s good to change the default behavior for a synchronous Put to not hang around in the write buffer.  However, I also think the default behavior for when a client calls flushCommits should be that the buffered commits are successfully committed, or an exception is thrown.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What do you think about using a separate setClearBufferOnFail method rather than overloading setAutoFlush?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
